1
00:00:09,708 --> 00:00:11,750
[JUNICHIRO]
I have YD.

2
00:00:11,833 --> 00:00:13,583
You've say never heard of it?

3
00:00:13,666 --> 00:00:14,458
What?

4
00:00:14,541 --> 00:00:15,958
I like wearing yukata on dates?

5
00:00:16,041 --> 00:00:17,833
Or yummy dinners?

6
00:00:17,916 --> 00:00:18,916
Wrong!

7
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:20,500
It's a debilitating illness

8
00:00:20,583 --> 00:00:23,416
where you can only do
what you yearn to do.

9
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:24,958
[JUNICHIRO]
You're happy doing what you love

10
00:00:25,041 --> 00:00:27,583
and you make a lot of other
people happy when you do it.

11
00:00:27,666 --> 00:00:29,458
It's nothing to be ashamed of.

12
00:00:29,541 --> 00:00:30,500
Please don't do this.

13
00:00:30,583 --> 00:00:32,791
But getting expelled
won't kill me.

14
00:00:32,875 --> 00:00:35,208
Losing my whole way
of life, on the other hand,

15
00:00:35,291 --> 00:00:36,666
is a fate worse than death.

16
00:00:36,750 --> 00:00:38,250
[JUNICHIRO]
Pay attention, Twin-Tails.

17
00:00:38,333 --> 00:00:41,250
'Cause this girl is about to
change the whole world!

18
00:00:41,333 --> 00:00:42,708
[KOYOMI]
In time, perhaps he can make

19
00:00:42,791 --> 00:00:44,875
this entire nation
shine as well.

20
00:00:44,958 --> 00:00:48,125
And I'll be there,
aiding his every step.

21
00:02:18,458 --> 00:02:21,083
Mornin'! Rise and shine!

22
00:02:21,166 --> 00:02:22,041
Hold on.

23
00:02:22,125 --> 00:02:23,166
No way.

24
00:02:23,250 --> 00:02:24,333
You're already up?

25
00:02:24,416 --> 00:02:25,458
[JUNICHIRO]
You mean "still up."

26
00:02:25,541 --> 00:02:28,166
Been doing some
overdue blogging.

27
00:02:28,250 --> 00:02:29,541
And post!

28
00:02:29,625 --> 00:02:31,541
[yawns]

29
00:02:31,625 --> 00:02:33,375
My work here is done.

30
00:02:33,458 --> 00:02:34,416
Time for some shut eye.

31
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:35,916
[growls]

32
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:38,833
Hey, could you hit
the lights for me?

33
00:02:38,916 --> 00:02:40,333
[yelps]

34
00:02:40,416 --> 00:02:41,916
You and your jokes.

35
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:45,666
You know full well today's your
first day teaching at my school!

36
00:02:50,333 --> 00:02:51,458
[KOYOMI]
We have officially revoked

37
00:02:51,541 --> 00:02:54,166
Kiriko Shikishima's
punishment at the behest

38
00:02:54,250 --> 00:02:57,000
of Mr. Junichiro Kagami,
who will be teaching at

39
00:02:57,083 --> 00:02:59,125
Icho Academy, starting today.

40
00:02:59,791 --> 00:03:01,750
[KOYOMI] All that's
left is for us to decide

41
00:03:01,833 --> 00:03:04,083
which grade he will be
teaching and for what hours,

42
00:03:04,166 --> 00:03:05,583
seeing that he's part-time.

43
00:03:05,666 --> 00:03:07,833
Do you have anything
you would like to contribute?

44
00:03:07,916 --> 00:03:09,666
Miss student council head?

45
00:03:09,750 --> 00:03:11,250
[MAKINA]
Yes, ma'am.

46
00:03:11,333 --> 00:03:13,458
I understand that man is your
favorite and you have high hopes

47
00:03:13,541 --> 00:03:15,416
for him and his
"amusing" methods.

48
00:03:15,500 --> 00:03:17,625
But I must once again
voice my concerns.

49
00:03:17,708 --> 00:03:20,791
I have no confidence in his
ability to educate others.

50
00:03:20,875 --> 00:03:23,500
Keeping that in mind, should he
get himself into any trouble,

51
00:03:23,583 --> 00:03:25,125
I, as the head of
the student council,

52
00:03:25,208 --> 00:03:27,208
will not be coming to his aid.

53
00:03:27,291 --> 00:03:28,791
[KOYOMI]
Good.

54
00:03:28,875 --> 00:03:31,041
That's precisely what
I wanted you to say.

55
00:03:31,125 --> 00:03:32,083
[gasps]

56
00:03:36,125 --> 00:03:38,625
Do me a favor and don't stand
so close to me at school.

57
00:03:38,708 --> 00:03:39,916
I'd really prefer no one know

58
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:42,166
you're my brother
if I can avoid it.

59
00:03:42,875 --> 00:03:44,583
Morning, Mr. Kagami!

60
00:03:44,666 --> 00:03:46,458
Oh, hey there, Potatoes!

61
00:03:46,541 --> 00:03:50,000
[chuckles] I just wanted to
say thank you for yesterday.

62
00:03:50,083 --> 00:03:51,000
If it weren't for you,

63
00:03:51,083 --> 00:03:52,750
I would've been
expelled for sure.

64
00:03:52,833 --> 00:03:53,916
Seriously.

65
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,541
No prob! My pleasure!

66
00:03:55,625 --> 00:03:56,958
So what's next?

67
00:03:57,041 --> 00:03:58,666
You gonna do a concert
for the school, Razor Girl?

68
00:03:58,750 --> 00:03:59,875
[gasps]

69
00:03:59,958 --> 00:04:01,416
[KIRIKO]
Shh! Shh! Shh!

70
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:03,750
Can you please keep my
stage persona to yourself?

71
00:04:03,833 --> 00:04:05,583
I'd like to keep it a secret!

72
00:04:05,666 --> 00:04:07,791
It's an underground,
indie kinda thing!

73
00:04:07,875 --> 00:04:09,458
[JUNICHIRO]
I hate to break it to you,

74
00:04:09,541 --> 00:04:11,125
but you're officially
mainstream.

75
00:04:11,208 --> 00:04:13,791
Holy crap! That's the
girl from the video!

76
00:04:13,875 --> 00:04:16,125
Legit! She's straight
up the Razor Girl!

77
00:04:16,208 --> 00:04:18,541
[STUDENTS chatter]

78
00:04:18,625 --> 00:04:20,833
[KIRIKO whimpers]

79
00:04:20,916 --> 00:04:22,500
[FEMALE STUDENT screams]

80
00:04:22,583 --> 00:04:23,291
[MALE STUDENT A]
What the-?

81
00:04:23,375 --> 00:04:23,958
[KIRIKO, JUNICHIRO grunt]

82
00:04:24,041 --> 00:04:25,541
[STUDENTS yelling]

83
00:04:25,625 --> 00:04:27,791
That must have been a
heck of an accident!

84
00:04:30,041 --> 00:04:31,916
[JUNICHIRO]
Huh? A footprint?

85
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,958
[SEIJURO]
Gotta watch where ya park.

86
00:04:38,125 --> 00:04:41,625
Ya never know if your
car's gonna get in my way.

87
00:04:41,708 --> 00:04:42,875
[JUNICHIRO yelps]

88
00:04:44,250 --> 00:04:46,625
[JUNICHIRO] What'd he do,
Falcon Kick that thing?

89
00:04:46,708 --> 00:04:49,500
Was this monster built
in a lab, or what?

90
00:04:49,583 --> 00:04:50,583
[MALE STUDENT D grunts]

91
00:04:53,541 --> 00:04:55,583
[MALE STUDENT D whimpers]

92
00:04:55,666 --> 00:04:56,791
[MALE STUDENT D grunts]

93
00:04:56,875 --> 00:04:58,583
You look like you're
trying to get in my way.

94
00:04:58,666 --> 00:04:59,583
[MALE STUDENT D]
Uh-uh...

95
00:04:59,666 --> 00:05:01,791
Mr. Kagami, you
have to stop him!

96
00:05:01,875 --> 00:05:03,708
You think I have a death
wish or something?

97
00:05:03,791 --> 00:05:05,875
The only reason I've been
able to stay alive this long

98
00:05:05,958 --> 00:05:08,375
is because I've kept away
from these types of peop--!

99
00:05:08,458 --> 00:05:09,208
[JUNICHIRO]
Heh...

100
00:05:09,291 --> 00:05:10,291
[MALE STUDENT D whimpers]

101
00:05:10,375 --> 00:05:12,666
Next time, watch where
you're goin'.

102
00:05:12,750 --> 00:05:13,875
Ya got it?

103
00:05:15,291 --> 00:05:19,125
[STUDENTS gasp]

104
00:05:19,208 --> 00:05:21,416
[MALE STUDENT D grunts]

105
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:23,250
[SEIJURO]
Hm?

106
00:05:23,333 --> 00:05:24,791
[JUNICHIRO]
Ow.

107
00:05:24,875 --> 00:05:26,833
all right! He did it!

108
00:05:26,916 --> 00:05:29,750
[JUNICHIRO grunts, gasps]

109
00:05:29,833 --> 00:05:31,541
[MALE STUDENT D gasps]
[JINICHIRO yells]

110
00:05:31,625 --> 00:05:34,291
[JUNICHIRO] Sergeant Saunders'
Revolver Cannon is missing!

111
00:05:34,375 --> 00:05:36,541
What is she going to do now?!

112
00:05:36,625 --> 00:05:37,083
[yelling]

113
00:05:37,166 --> 00:05:38,500
You're kidding!

114
00:05:38,583 --> 00:05:41,125
Where did it go? It has to
be around here somewhere!

115
00:05:41,208 --> 00:05:43,541
C'mon, you Cyborg monster,
don't just stand there!

116
00:05:43,625 --> 00:05:45,250
You're the reason the
Revolver Cannon's missing.

117
00:05:45,333 --> 00:05:47,166
The least you can do
is help look for it!

118
00:05:47,250 --> 00:05:48,666
[SEIJURO]
Hey, freak-show.

119
00:05:48,750 --> 00:05:50,000
[JUNICHIRO] Sergeant Saunders
isn't going to be able to

120
00:05:50,083 --> 00:05:51,500
--transform without that cannon!
--[SEIJURO growls]

121
00:05:51,583 --> 00:05:53,541
[SEIJURO]
Don't get in my way!

122
00:05:53,625 --> 00:05:54,708
Ah! Oh, no!

123
00:05:54,791 --> 00:05:55,875
[yells]

124
00:05:55,958 --> 00:05:57,125
[SUZUNE yells]

125
00:05:57,583 --> 00:05:59,416
[JUNICHIRO]
Where could it be?

126
00:05:59,500 --> 00:06:01,166
[STUDENTS murmur]

127
00:06:01,250 --> 00:06:02,041
[KIRIKO gasps]

128
00:06:02,125 --> 00:06:03,041
[growls]

129
00:06:03,125 --> 00:06:04,583
You need to back up, Nanami.

130
00:06:04,666 --> 00:06:07,125
I'm the only one who gets
to beat up my brother!

131
00:06:07,208 --> 00:06:10,416
[JUNICHIRO grunts]
Where could it have gone?

132
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:12,666
Wait. Suzune's related
to that guy?

133
00:06:12,750 --> 00:06:14,125
[FEMALE STUDENT A]
He's such a freakazoid!

134
00:06:14,208 --> 00:06:15,333
[MALE STUDENT A]
Totally!

135
00:06:15,416 --> 00:06:17,375
Heh. You tellin' me
this man-child cryin'

136
00:06:17,458 --> 00:06:20,208
on the ground over some
stupid toy is your big bro?

137
00:06:20,291 --> 00:06:22,291
I shoulda known
he was a Kagami.

138
00:06:22,375 --> 00:06:24,875
Yeah, he may be an idiot
otaku who's obsessed

139
00:06:24,958 --> 00:06:28,708
with toys and cartoons, but at
least he's proud of who he is.

140
00:06:28,791 --> 00:06:30,666
Maybe that doesn't
mean a whole lot to you,

141
00:06:30,750 --> 00:06:32,166
but I'll tell you one thing.

142
00:06:32,250 --> 00:06:34,791
At least he doesn't take his
hurt feelings out on others!

143
00:06:36,458 --> 00:06:37,875
How cute.

144
00:06:37,958 --> 00:06:40,250
If you're done preachin',
get your stick outta my face.

145
00:06:40,333 --> 00:06:42,500
It's in my hand,
not your face.

146
00:06:43,708 --> 00:06:44,708
[SEIJURO grunts]

147
00:06:44,791 --> 00:06:46,375
[SEIJURO, SUZUNE yell]

148
00:06:46,458 --> 00:06:47,500
That's enough!

149
00:06:47,583 --> 00:06:48,541
[BOTH gasp]

150
00:06:50,791 --> 00:06:51,791
[FEMALE STUDENT A]
Uh-oh.

151
00:06:51,875 --> 00:06:53,250
[MALE STUDENT A]
They're in trouble now!

152
00:06:53,333 --> 00:06:55,750
Thank goodness you're here!

153
00:06:55,833 --> 00:06:58,166
Sergeant Saunders' Revolver
Cannon has gone missing.

154
00:06:58,250 --> 00:07:00,375
you need to tell everyone
to help look for it.

155
00:07:00,458 --> 00:07:01,833
Sounds simple enough.

156
00:07:01,916 --> 00:07:03,708
Everyone, if I may
have your attention,

157
00:07:03,791 --> 00:07:06,541
I would like to introduce a new
teacher starting today:

158
00:07:06,625 --> 00:07:08,291
Mr. Junichiro Kagami.

159
00:07:08,375 --> 00:07:09,375
[MALE STUDENT B]
No way!

160
00:07:09,458 --> 00:07:10,416
[FEMALE STUDENT B]
But he's so weird!

161
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:11,583
[KOYOMI]
He has requested that I

162
00:07:11,666 --> 00:07:13,458
share a message on his behalf.

163
00:07:13,541 --> 00:07:14,750
[JUNICHIRO]
Mmhm, Mmhm.

164
00:07:14,833 --> 00:07:17,083
"I started this fight,
I'll finish it.

165
00:07:17,166 --> 00:07:19,000
Leave my little
sister out of this.

166
00:07:19,083 --> 00:07:21,208
As your teacher,
I will be your opponent,

167
00:07:21,291 --> 00:07:23,291
and no one else will interfere."

168
00:07:23,375 --> 00:07:24,000
[KOYOMI]
End quote.

169
00:07:24,083 --> 00:07:24,750
[SUZUNE]
Huh?

170
00:07:24,833 --> 00:07:25,833
[JUNICHIRO]
Mmhm.

171
00:07:25,916 --> 00:07:28,416
[gasps]
Wait, I said what now?!

172
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:29,791
[SEIJURO]
Interesting.

173
00:07:29,875 --> 00:07:31,291
Hm.

174
00:07:31,375 --> 00:07:32,708
Hey. Listen.

175
00:07:32,791 --> 00:07:35,625
Your showdown will be
in seventy-two hours.

176
00:07:35,708 --> 00:07:37,500
The rules are simple:
there are none.

177
00:07:37,583 --> 00:07:40,583
Victory is determined by making
the other admit defeat.

178
00:07:40,666 --> 00:07:42,041
[SEIJURO]
Hm...

179
00:07:47,416 --> 00:07:51,500
Figures. You'd think I'd be
used to your crazy ideas by now.

180
00:07:51,583 --> 00:07:52,583
Fine, three days,

181
00:07:52,666 --> 00:07:54,583
I'll be looking forward to it.

182
00:07:55,416 --> 00:07:56,458
Unless you know
the Song of Time,

183
00:07:56,541 --> 00:07:57,583
I'm dead in three days!

184
00:07:57,666 --> 00:07:58,875
[SUZUNE gasps]

185
00:07:58,958 --> 00:08:00,750
Miss Hiiragi. I was
hoping you would actually

186
00:08:00,833 --> 00:08:02,666
put some consideration
into this!

187
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:05,083
But you just publicly named
him a teacher on a whim.

188
00:08:05,166 --> 00:08:07,000
you should be more
careful than that!

189
00:08:07,083 --> 00:08:08,708
assure you, my consideration

190
00:08:08,791 --> 00:08:10,666
was quite careful
and done at length.

191
00:08:10,750 --> 00:08:12,083
Liar, liar, pants on fire!

192
00:08:12,166 --> 00:08:13,583
Of course!

193
00:08:13,666 --> 00:08:15,333
He's assigned to teach my grade.

194
00:08:15,416 --> 00:08:17,250
But it's probably for the best.

195
00:08:17,333 --> 00:08:19,666
This way, things should
be easier for you.

196
00:08:19,750 --> 00:08:21,958
Why, because I'll have
you there with me?

197
00:08:22,041 --> 00:08:25,250
[SUZUNE] No, because my class
has less kids in it right now.

198
00:08:25,333 --> 00:08:28,791
About half my grade's been
sent to the hospital by Nanami.

199
00:08:28,875 --> 00:08:30,416
[gasps]

200
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:31,583
[groans]

201
00:08:31,666 --> 00:08:32,708
Jeez, what now?

202
00:08:32,791 --> 00:08:34,166
Mr. Kagami!

203
00:08:34,250 --> 00:08:36,000
Someone help me get
him to the nurse's office!

204
00:08:36,083 --> 00:08:38,666
Hey, everyone, I found
the Revolver Cannon.

205
00:08:38,750 --> 00:08:39,916
[sighs]

206
00:08:48,166 --> 00:08:51,000
These are the last few
fleeting moments of my life.

207
00:08:51,083 --> 00:08:54,041
Soon, I will be but a memory
just like that leaf.

208
00:08:54,125 --> 00:08:56,208
No quarters, no continues!

209
00:08:56,291 --> 00:08:58,541
Will you please stop being
so dramatic already?

210
00:08:58,625 --> 00:09:00,208
Seriously, I can handle Nanami.

211
00:09:00,291 --> 00:09:02,708
There's no reason for you
to get so worked up, okay?

212
00:09:02,791 --> 00:09:03,916
[sobbing]

213
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:05,041
Stop crying!

214
00:09:05,125 --> 00:09:06,666
We need a plan.

215
00:09:06,750 --> 00:09:08,875
And I think I've
got just the idea!

216
00:09:08,958 --> 00:09:10,250
I met someone online

217
00:09:10,333 --> 00:09:12,666
who's a real pro at handling
situations like this.

218
00:09:12,750 --> 00:09:14,833
I think we should
ask for their help!

219
00:09:16,958 --> 00:09:18,666
[SUZUNE]
I'm curious.

220
00:09:18,750 --> 00:09:21,166
What do you think
Kiriko's friend is like?

221
00:09:21,250 --> 00:09:22,625
[JUNICHIRO]
I'm hoping like a top tier

222
00:09:22,708 --> 00:09:25,083
street fighting character.

223
00:09:25,166 --> 00:09:26,125
[SUZUNE]
Hmm...

224
00:09:29,791 --> 00:09:30,166
[SUZUNE sighs]

225
00:09:32,583 --> 00:09:34,500
[MAIDS]
Welcome home, milady!

226
00:09:35,625 --> 00:09:37,625
[KIRIKO]
Hey, you made it!

227
00:09:37,708 --> 00:09:38,750
[giggles]

228
00:09:38,833 --> 00:09:40,333
[GIRL] I'm surprised
you contacted me.

229
00:09:40,416 --> 00:09:43,000
You know I'm not involved with
that kinda stuff anymore.

230
00:09:43,083 --> 00:09:44,583
[JUNICHIRO]
It's a girl.

231
00:09:44,666 --> 00:09:46,583
[GIRL] There should be a rule
about not dragging people back

232
00:09:46,666 --> 00:09:48,666
to their past after
they've moved on.

233
00:09:48,750 --> 00:09:50,416
[JUNICHIRO]
Wait, I know this voice!

234
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:52,083
You okay?
You're acting weird, dude.

235
00:09:52,166 --> 00:09:55,500
Even if there were, don't forget
what you told me the other day.

236
00:09:55,583 --> 00:09:57,291
"You can't get by
in life by doing

237
00:09:57,375 --> 00:09:59,458
nothing but following
the rules!" am I right?

238
00:09:59,541 --> 00:10:00,375
[JUNICHIRO gasps]

239
00:10:00,458 --> 00:10:01,500
[GIRL]
Yeah, but people like me

240
00:10:01,583 --> 00:10:03,708
are supposed to
say stuff like that.

241
00:10:03,791 --> 00:10:04,750
But you?

242
00:10:04,833 --> 00:10:06,125
You need a bit
more training first!

243
00:10:06,208 --> 00:10:07,708
[clattering]

244
00:10:07,791 --> 00:10:08,750
[gasps]

245
00:10:10,083 --> 00:10:12,000
No! Why's it Face-Punch?

246
00:10:12,083 --> 00:10:13,458
What's Face-Punch?

247
00:10:13,541 --> 00:10:14,208
Face-Punch?

248
00:10:14,291 --> 00:10:16,541
[laughs nervously]

