490
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:01,000
[SEIJURO]
His arms look like twigs,

491
00:20:01,083 --> 00:20:03,583
when they used to
look like tree trunks.

492
00:20:06,166 --> 00:20:08,208
[NURSE] Mr. Nanami, hold on!
[SEIJURO] This isn't him.

493
00:20:08,291 --> 00:20:10,166
This isn't my dad!

494
00:20:13,250 --> 00:20:15,708
[SEIJURO] He would never
deny his own way of life.

495
00:20:15,791 --> 00:20:18,000
He'd never give up like that.

496
00:20:19,625 --> 00:20:21,291
[SEIJURO]
Dad would never lose!

497
00:20:22,541 --> 00:20:26,375
Hey, tough guy!
Back up. Let's talk.

498
00:20:26,458 --> 00:20:28,916
[SEIJURO]
And neither will I.

499
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:31,500
[DELINQUENT] So what
are you waiting for?

500
00:20:31,583 --> 00:20:34,958
You owe me an apology,
now let's hear it!

501
00:20:35,041 --> 00:20:37,083
[growls]

502
00:20:37,166 --> 00:20:39,958
[SEIJURO] You shouldn't
have got in my way!

503
00:20:44,208 --> 00:20:46,333
[SEIJURO]
I'm happy for you, Miss Kanou.

504
00:20:46,416 --> 00:20:49,875
But there's no place
where I belong.

505
00:20:49,958 --> 00:20:52,250
All I know is, right now,

506
00:20:52,333 --> 00:20:56,541
I have to move forward,
but he's standing in my way.

507
00:20:58,416 --> 00:21:00,625
[SEIJURO]
I'll never back down.

508
00:21:08,125 --> 00:21:10,500
[SEIJURO] I can't believe
you actually showed up.

509
00:21:10,583 --> 00:21:12,291
That's what I was thinking.

510
00:21:12,375 --> 00:21:14,666
You're looking pretty worn out.

511
00:21:14,750 --> 00:21:16,083
I've been practicing this game

512
00:21:16,166 --> 00:21:18,000
for the last two days
without stopping.

513
00:21:18,083 --> 00:21:19,208
Not even for sleep.

514
00:21:19,291 --> 00:21:20,750
But it's all good,

515
00:21:20,833 --> 00:21:23,166
I got plenty of fight left in
me to go one game with you.

516
00:21:23,250 --> 00:21:25,791
[JUNICHIRO] Good. I was
a bit worried, actually.

517
00:21:25,875 --> 00:21:27,750
[SEIJURO]
Uh...

518
00:21:27,833 --> 00:21:29,458
Because we're gonna
play soccer now,

519
00:21:29,541 --> 00:21:33,125
and I want you at your best.
So you sure you're up for it?

520
00:21:33,208 --> 00:21:34,875
Wait. But you said--?

521
00:21:34,958 --> 00:21:38,250
That we were playing a game,
but I never specified which.

522
00:21:38,333 --> 00:21:41,791
It's not my fault you assumed we
were gonna play video games.

523
00:21:41,875 --> 00:21:44,083
'Cause soccer's
on the itinerary.

524
00:21:44,166 --> 00:21:47,250
[growls]
You bastard!

525
00:21:47,333 --> 00:21:48,875
[growls]

526
00:21:50,250 --> 00:21:51,375
[chuckles]

527
00:23:31,125 --> 00:23:33,583
[SEIJURO]
The Cyborg Seijuro Nanami here.

528
00:23:33,666 --> 00:23:35,916
In order to protect
peace on Earth, I will--

529
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:37,333
Wait! Dammit!

530
00:23:37,416 --> 00:23:40,250
This Otaku Teacher's
getting into my head!

531
00:23:40,333 --> 00:23:42,708
Next episode, our
teams go head-to-head

532
00:23:42,791 --> 00:23:45,250
in a no-holds-barred
soccer match.

533
00:23:45,333 --> 00:23:46,666
Winner take all.

534
00:23:46,750 --> 00:23:49,708
Loser becomes a
lifelong servant!

535
00:23:49,791 --> 00:23:54,083
Period six, "An Amusing View."
You say I'm not alone?

536
00:23:54,166 --> 00:23:57,083
Ha! You don't know
anything about me!

